{
  "stem": "14060.6",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I do not remember that we were actually going absolutely starving hungry.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We had limited supplies of things.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I cannot tell you in all honesty how the supplies came into the ghetto, or what was allocated.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Presumably certain rations were given against payment, which they demanded for every-- they practically demanded to pay your fare into Auschwitz, not that they did.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And our existence was pretty miserable there already.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "That was no fun anymore.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And, and everybody went around with a drawn face and hoping what's going to happen.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And we, we, we still knew about the Allied landings on the 6th of June in 1944.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "We were still there in the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And we were hoping for the best, that it's literally coming to an end, and nothing serious may happen.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And the story was that we will be taken to work in the east.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "The fear in the people was that we are taken to Poland.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Let me just tell you the actual deportation train, and then I want to come back to this question of Poland otherwise.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "It was on a summer afternoon when we were told that we have to go in groups, walk to the station, which was maybe 10 minutes walk from where we were.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "It was very close to our home, just up towards the [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "That's the resort part of the town.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And we went to the daily [INAUDIBLE], which means the southern station.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And we were lined up and then told to get in, and 80, 90 people.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "I remember the people who were in our train.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And I got into a corner.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
